Revenant icefiends are a type of monster, that inhabits the Forinthry Dungeon, along with all other revenants. The Forinthry Dungeon is a part of the Wilderness so it is possible to be attacked by other players here if opted into PvP.

Like all revenants, they can restore lifepoints quickly, can cure themselves of poison and react quickly to a player's protection prayers. When below 50% health, revenant icefiends will "eat" to heal 675 lifepoints from their limited supply of food. For a full description of the healing mechanic see the revenants page.

Drops[edit | edit source]

Drop rates estimated based on 13,950 samples from the Drop Log Project, unless otherwise cited.

Revenant drops are not affected by luck. There are only two ways to increase the drop rate of revenant items: completion of the elite Wilderness achievements which gives a 5% increased chance for revenant drops, and revenant drop enhancers, which give a 10% increased chance. Both boosts can be in effect at the same time.

Wilderness drop table[edit | edit source]

This monster has access to the Wilderness shared loot table, which is a tertiary drop. To access the table, it has to be killed inside the Wilderness.
Luck-enhancing items are not required to access the table, but do increase the chance of doing so, as does doing higher-level content.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 17 April 2023 (Update):
    • Fixed the issue of incorrect souls being captured by Ushabti.
  • patch 11 April 2023 (Update):
    • Can be killed as part of the new undead slayer task.
  • update 10 December 2007 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The examine for a revenant icefiend is slightly different from most other revenants (excluding revenant hellhounds, pyrefiends, imps, and demons). Its examine says that it is the essence of an icefiend slain during the God Wars, as opposed to the ghost of an icefiend slain during the God Wars. These five revenants are similar in that they are all demonic.
